      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SLIP THE JAB (2) comes here off a 75-day break where he hasn't been sighted publicly, but he drops right back in grade. He's been solid in Open 3YO company on a Saturday and comes back to this event with a favourable set up for Parnham. Finds the right race today and can get back to winning ways. NEW TARGET (3) was just fair on the heavy deck two back before a 4.3L defeat last start on the quick turnaround at Belmont. This shapes similarly for her today, though the firmer footing on offer should be a big bonus for her. Expecting an improved effort. BRAZEN BUTCHER (1) ended up 2.3L off the winner last start after jumping the race fave in stronger company than he meets today. Pike sticks, with an inside draw a big tick and the blinkers going on first time. He ticks plenty of boxes. SHARPASSA (4) comes here with a solid trial under her belt and a forward showing is expected. BRICINI (5) can go one better this time without surprising.",
